'''Badam Chaloq''' ({{lang-fa|<U+0628><U+0627><U+062F><U+0627><U+0645> <U+0686><U+0627><U+0644><U+0642>}}, also [[Romanize]]d as '''B<U+0101>d<U+0101>m Ch<U+0101>loq'''; also known as '''Badam Chalegh''' and '''B<U+0101>d<U+0101>m Ch<U+0101>l<U+016B>q''')<ref>{{GEOnet3|-3054379|Badam Chaloq}}</ref> is a village in [[Aq Kahriz Rural District]], [[Nowbaran District]], [[Saveh County]], [[Markazi Province]], [[Iran]]. At the 2006 census, its population was 273, in 91 families.<ref>{{IranCensus2006|00}}</ref>  

